      • isProcessingError

        public boolean isProcessingError()
        Determine if any processing errors occurred. isError() will always return true if this returns true.

        Returns:
        true if any processing errors occurred, false otherwise.

      • isValidationError

        public boolean isValidationError()
        Determine if all validation checks passed based on the validation mode of the DataProcessor. If validation mode is Off, this will always return false. This is only meaningful when isProcessingError() is false. isError() will always return true if this return true.

        Returns:
        true if any validation errors occurred, false otherwise.

      • location

      • result

        public org.jdom2.Document result()
                          throws InvalidUsageException
        Deprecated. Use parse(ReadableByteChannel, InfosetInputter) to parse the data and get the infoset representation from the InfosetOutputter. Since 2.0.0.
        Get the resulting infoset as a jdom2 Document

        Returns:
        a jdom2 Document representing the DFDL infoset for the parsed data
        Throws:
        InvalidUsageException - if you call this when isError is true because in that case there is no result document.
